<HEAD><title>Cost of Government Day Overview -- ATR</title></HEAD>
<BODY Bgcolor=#FFFFFF>
<BODY ALINK="$XXX">
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="cal.gif">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+4>A<FONT SIZE=+3>mericans</FONT> f<FONT SIZE=+3> or</FONT> T<FONT SIZE=+3>ax</FONT> R<FONT SIZE=+3>eform</FONT> F<FONT SIZE=+3>oundation</FONT></CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<font size=+3><bold><center>Cost of Government Day</font></bold></center><hr noshade>
</FONT>
<FONT=+1>
<center><A HREF="#HISTORY">|HISTORY</A>
<A HREF="#DEFINITION">|DEFINITION|</A><br>
<A HREF="#Facts About Regulation">Facts about Regulation|</a>
<A HREF="#Regulatory Horror Stories">Regulatory Horror Stories|</a>
<A HREF="#An Agenda for Reform in 1996">
An Agenda for Reform in 1996|</a></center>

<P>COGD 1996 is July 3<P></FONT>

	Cost of Government Day is the date of the calendar year, counting from January  1, that Americans have earned enough money to pay off the  total financial burden of government, including all state and federal spending and  regulatory costs.<P>
	The money we send to the government on April 15th is only the visible tip of a much larger iceberg.  Politicians have learned to circumvent the watchful eye of anti-tax voters by enacting hidden taxes--regulationsand government mandates.  Costly government programs, such as the Americans with Disabilities Act and family leave legislation, do not show up in the federal or state budgets.  But they do cost money.<P>
 	This year, every American taxpayer will work until July 3rd--more than half way through the  year--to pay off his or  her share of government imposed financial costs. The total cost of government in 1996 is estimated at
 $3.38 trillion. That's $13,000 for every man, woman and child in 
America. Of this total, nearly $1 trillion results from federal and
state regulation. The federal government is responsible for more than
 $739 million in hidden regulatory taxes this year alone. That's more
 than $2,800 for every man, woman and child in America.<P>
	To find out  more about Cost of Government Day 1995, call Americans for Tax Reform Foundation at 202-785-0266.<P>




<CAPTION ALIGN=TOP><FONT SIZE=+1><BOLD><a name="HISTORY">Cost of Government Day History</a></BOLD></FONT></CAPTION><P>
