<html><head><title> Civil Rights Initiatives--8/8/95 -- ATR</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><h3>CIVIL RIGHTS INITIATIVES
  8/8/95</h3></center>
<HR>

<a href="/atr/1.html">ATR Home</a><P>
<a name="Index"<P></a>
<center><b>States with civil rights initiative measures</b><br>
<a href="#California">California</a>
 | <a href="#Colorado">Colorado</a>
 | <a href="#Florida">Florida</a>
 | <a href="#Idaho">Idaho</a>
 | <a href="#Maine">Maine</a>  
 | <a href="#Massachusetts">Massachusetts</a>
 | <a href="#Michigan">Michigan</a>
 | <a href="#Oregon">Oregon</a>
 | <a href="#Washington">Washington</a>
<P>
<hr size="6"></center>
<pre>
<font size="+3"><B>STATE	LEGISLATION -SPONSOR</b></font> 
<hr size="6">
<a name="California"></a>CALIFORNIA	-California Civil Rights Initiative
			(1) ends Affirmative Action programs; 
			no discrimination based on race, sex, 
			or color.  -Gelman
		-California Civil Rights Initiative
			(2) similar to CCRI(1) -Reede
		-Civil Rights Initiative
			(3) stops quotas, equal opportunity,
			Anti-Affirmative Action   -Thompson
		-Economic and educational opportunity, pro- 
			Affirmative Action   -Jackson
<hr>
<a name="Colorado"></a>COLORADO	-No discrimination in employment based on 
			sexual orientation  -Gilbert
<hr>
<a name="Florida"></a>FLORIDA 	-No state discrimination   -Martin
<hr>
<a name="Idaho"></a>IDAHO		-Family and Child Protection Act Anti-
			Homosexual rights  -Walton
<hr>
<a name="Massachusetts"></a>MASSACHUSETTS	-Ending quotas and promoting equal 
			opportunity  -Jacoby
<hr>
<a name="Maine"></a>MAINE		-Limitation of protected classes   -Cosby
<hr>
<a name="Michigan"></a>MICHIGAN	-Civil rights   -Tuttle
<hr>
<a name="Oregon"></a>OREGON		-Ends most Affirmative Action   -Selby
		-Repeals set-asides   -Selby
		-The Minority Status and Child Protection 
			Act of 1996  -Mabon
		-Stop Minority Status Act  -Mabon
		-No minority status based on sexual 
			behavior  -Mabon
<hr>
<a name="Washington"></a>WASHINGTON	-Repeal Affirmative Action   -Taber
		-Anti-gay legislation  -Bronson
</pre><hr size="6">
PROVIDED BY KOLT ZIMMERMANN JONES 
